<text id="02-output-contract" title="Web Scraping Resilience Output Contract" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="800" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the resilience config artefact. The scrape consumes one config per source; missing fields are rejected at start-up.</summary>

  <section title="JSON Schema (draft-07)">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/web-scraping-resilience.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["artefact_id", "source", "delay_ms_min", "delay_ms_max", "max_retries", "base_delay_ms", "safe_extract_timeout_ms", "anti_detect_enabled", "crash_recover_enabled", "concurrency_cap", "version", "last_reviewed"],
  "properties": {
    "artefact_id":             {"type": "string", "pattern": "^wsrr-[a-z0-9-]{6,}$"},
    "source":                  {"type": "string", "minLength": 1},
    "delay_ms_min":            {"type": "integer", "minimum": 100, "maximum": 60000},
    "delay_ms_max":            {"type": "integer", "minimum": 100, "maximum": 60000},
    "max_retries":             {"type": "integer", "minimum": 0, "maximum": 5},
    "base_delay_ms":           {"type": "integer", "minimum": 100, "maximum": 10000},
    "safe_extract_timeout_ms": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 100, "maximum": 5000},
    "anti_detect_enabled":     {"type": "boolean"},
    "crash_recover_enabled":   {"type": "boolean"},
    "concurrency_cap":         {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1, "maximum": 50},
    "stealth_lib":             {"type": ["string", "null"]},
    "version":                 {"type": "string", "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$"},
    "last_reviewed":           {"type": "string", "format": "date"}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "wsrr-news-2026-05",
  "source": "example.com/news",
  "delay_ms_min": 1000,
  "delay_ms_max": 3000,
  "max_retries": 5,
  "base_delay_ms": 500,
  "safe_extract_timeout_ms": 5000,
  "anti_detect_enabled": true,
  "crash_recover_enabled": true,
  "concurrency_cap": 3,
  "stealth_lib": "playwright-stealth",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "last_reviewed": "2026-05-23"
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "artefact_id": "news",
  "source": "example.com/news",
  "delay_ms_min": 0,
  "delay_ms_max": 0,
  "max_retries": 100,
  "base_delay_ms": 50,
  "safe_extract_timeout_ms": 30000,
  "anti_detect_enabled": false,
  "crash_recover_enabled": false,
  "concurrency_cap": 100,
  "version": "1.0",
  "last_reviewed": "today"
}
]]></code>
    <note>artefact_id missing wsrr- prefix; delay_ms_min/max both 0 (tight loop violates r1); max_retries=100 exceeds cap 5 (r2 violation); safe_extract_timeout_ms=30000 exceeds 5000 (r3 violation); anti_detect_enabled + crash_recover_enabled both false (r4+r5 violation); concurrency_cap=100 above max 50; version + last_reviewed malformed.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <antipattern>
      <description>delay_ms_min == delay_ms_max (no jitter).</description>
      <reason>Fixed-interval requests fingerprint; r1 demands a jitter range.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>max_retries &gt; 5.</description>
      <reason>r2 caps at 5; longer retries delay the run unboundedly without raising success rate.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>safe_extract_timeout_ms &gt; 5000.</description>
      <reason>r3 caps at 5 s; longer timeouts compound across a slow page into minute-long row latency.</reason>
    </antipattern>
  </section>

  <reference path="templates/web-scraping-resilience.json">Schema canonical location.</reference>
  <reference path="scripts/validate-web-scraping-resilience.py">Validator that enforces this contract.</reference>
</text>
